description: Life-changing events like the birth of a child, the purchase of a new home, or a lottery win could threaten the survival of a new business venture, research from Edith Cowan University (ECU) has found. The work is published in the International Entrepreneurship and Management Journal.
title: Baby bonuses and wedding bells: How life's big moments can challenge startups

description: Just southwest of Boise lies one of the last vast swaths of solitude in the United States.
title: The secret is out: The world found the Owyhees—Advocates say it's time to protect the land

description: Two orphaned Black bears have been released back into the wild, ending their nearly year-long rehabilitation at the San Diego Humane Society's Ramona Wildlife Center, according to officials.
title: Two orphaned Black bears released back into wild after rehabilitation by San Diego Humane Society

description: Published today in the Alcheringa: An Australasian Journal of Palaeontology, evidence of an "Age of Monotremes" has been unearthed by a team of Australian scientists at the Australian Museum (AM), Museums Victoria and Australian Opal Centre.
title: New fossils provide evidence for an 'Age of Monotremes'

description: Using observations by NASA's TESS (Transiting Exoplanet Survey Satellite) and many other facilities, two international teams of astronomers have discovered a planet between the sizes of Earth and Venus only 40 light-years away. Multiple factors make it a candidate well-suited for further study using NASA's James Webb Space Telescope.
title: TESS finds intriguing world sized between Earth and Venus

description: Entrepreneurs are the lifeblood of any innovative economy.
title: Life's big moments can impact an entrepreneur's success—but not always in the way you'd expect

description: Will clouds help cool or warm our world in the years ahead? The EarthCARE satellite will soon blast off on a mission to find out, aiming to investigate what role clouds could play in the fight against climate change.
title: EarthCARE satellite to probe how clouds affect climate

description: Tens of thousands of Bangladeshis left their coastal villages Sunday for concrete storm shelters further inland as the low-lying nation prepared for the expected landfall of an intense cyclone, officials said.
title: Thousands flee as cyclone heads towards Bangladesh

description: Although the grizzly is featured prominently on the California state flag, the golden bear has been extinct in the wild since the 1920s.
title: Setting minimum targets for wildlife conservation excludes restoration and ecosystem management, researcher argues
